## OD-3 permissions split (pending product sign-off)

- **Invariant enforcer:** `PermissionRuleEngine` owns all allow/deny gates (Phase 5 migration from `permissions-helper`)
- **Presenter only:** `permissions.presenter` assembles booleans + i18n disabled-reason keys (`voteDisabled.*`, etc.)
- **Phase 3 interim:** engine stub methods delegate to `PermissionGatesPort`; adapter is sole `permissions-helper` importer
- **Sign-off gate:** `.index/architecture/od3-matrix-signed.yaml` must be product-signed before Phase 5 permissions merge

## Common Mistakes

вқҢ Importing backend runtime code from `api/` in `web/`
вң… Type-only import bridge: `api/apps/meriter/src/trpc/types.ts` re-exports `AppRouter` from `./router`. The web tRPC client imports it from there via a relative path (`web/src/lib/trpc/client.ts`).
вқҢ Duplicating types instead of using shared-types (especially `ResourcePermissions` вҖ” use `libs/shared-types` only)
вқҢ Domain service importing `trpc/helpers` or `api-v1/*`
вқҢ Cross-router imports (Zone 9) вҖ” use a shared use case instead
